<p><a name="Notes" id="Notes"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Tort&amp;action=edit&amp;section=21" title="Edit section: Notes">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Notes</span></h2>
<div class="references-small references-column-count references-column-count-2" style="-moz-column-count:2; column-count:2;">
<ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-0"><b><a href="#cite_ref-0" title="">^</a></b> "Tort" is the Norman word for a "wrong." As traditionally used, this kind of wrong is distinct from a contractual or criminal wrong. See: G. Edward White, <i>Tort Law in America: An Intellectual History</i>, (2003) p. xxiii.</li>
